Your teammate has asked you to review the code below, which is adding a credit to an account balance in Cloud Datastore. Which improvement should you suggest your teammate make?<codeblock>
public Entity creditAccount (long accountId, long creditAmount) {
Entity account = datastore.get
(keyFactory.newKey (accountId));
account = Entity.builder (account).set( "balance", account.getLong ("balance") + creditAmount).build()
datastore.put (account);
return account;
}</codeblock>

Your teammate has asked you to review the code below. Its purpose is to efficiently add a large number of small rows to a BigQuery table.<codeblock>
BigQuery service = BigQueryOptions.newBuilder().build().getService();

public void writeToBigQuery(Collection<Map<String, String>> rows) {
	for (Map<String, String> row : rows) {
		InsertAllRequest insertRequest = InsertAllRequest.newBuilder("datasetId", "tableId",
				InsertAllRequest.RowToInsert.of(row)).build();

		service.insertAll(insertRequest);
	}
}</codeblock>
Which improvement should you suggest your teammate make?
